sentences.english: The dreaded wood-eating shipworm is invading northern Europe's Baltic Sea.
sentences.chinese: 可怕的喫木頭的船蛆正在侵襲北歐的波羅的海。

sentences.english: Baltic Birch enclosure with Polyurea coating.
sentences.chinese: 波羅的海樺木箱體，聚脲塗料。

sentences.english: Important elements of his fleet were lying in the harbors of northern France, in Norway and in the Baltic Sea.
sentences.chinese: 艦隊主力亦隱藏於法國北部，挪威及波羅的海諸港中。

sentences.english: The port of London laid an embargo on all ships coming from the Baltic.
sentences.chinese: 倫敦港禁止所有來自波羅的海的船隻入港。

sentences.english: Snow-covered fishing and sailing boats are seen on the frozen Baltic Sea in Hel, northern Poland, January 24, 2006.
sentences.chinese: 在波蘭瀕波羅的海的海爾城，大雪淹沒了漁船與帆船。

sentences.english: The Baltic was still frozen in May.
sentences.chinese: 波羅的海5月時仍然處在封凍狀態。

sentences.english: A city of southeast Sweden on western Gotland Island on the Baltic Sea.
sentences.chinese: 瑞典東南部一城市，位於波羅的海的哥特蘭島西岸。

sentences.english: How do you conquer the world with a navy that can’t get out of the Baltic Sea?
sentences.chinese: 就憑一支連波羅的海都出不去的海軍，如何征服世界？

sentences.english: Lubeck (or Liubke, as it was called) was a small, unimportant trading village on the Baltic Sea. It had no army.
sentences.chinese: 呂貝克，在波羅的海並不重要的一個交易村莊。

sentences.english: As non coastal harbor it is, Hamburg is the port between the North Sea and the Baltic Sea.
sentences.chinese: 漢堡港雖不靠海，卻是北海和波羅的海兩海之港。

sentences.english: And almost always wind wafts endless clouds from the Baltics.
sentences.chinese: 還有那波羅的海刮來的風，總是帶來變化無窮的雲彩。

sentences.english: The Baltic Sea is the largest brackish water basin in the world.
sentences.chinese: 波羅的海是世界上最大的微鹹水盆地。

sentences.english: Para-Medic: I see you've got yourself a Baltic Hornets' nest.
sentences.chinese: 我見你打到一個波羅的海蜂巢。

sentences.english: Birch plywood enclosure finished in black semi-matte textured paint.
sentences.chinese: 波羅的海樺木箱體，黑色半啞光粗質噴漆。

sentences.english: Just buy property in this Baltic State.
sentences.chinese: 那就在這個波羅的海小國買套房子吧。

sentences.english: Comprised of hunters from throughout the Baltic region, these men seek to earn a living serving in local militias and armies.
sentences.chinese: 這些波羅的海獵戶爲了生計需要，毅然投軍作戰。
